<br>[学习本文需要基础词汇量：<x-rating>6</x-rating>,000 ]<br>[本次分析采用基础词汇量：<x-rating2>4</x-rating2>,000 ]<br><p style="line-height: 150%">伯32:1 <br>So these three men <x-group group="ceaseXto"><span style="box-shadow: 0px 3px white, 0px 4px #00BFFF;">ceased to</span></x-group> answer Job, because he was <x-word word="righteous"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #FF0000;">righteous</span></x-word> in his own eyes.<br>于是，这三个人因约伯自以为义，就不再回答他。<br><br><br>伯32:2 <br>Then was <x-word word="kindled"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #800000;">kindled</span></x-word> the <x-word word="wrath"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #FF0000;">wrath</span></x-word> of <x-word word="elihu"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #0000FF;">Elihu</span></x-word> the son of <x-word word="barachel"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #0000FF;">Barachel</span></x-word> the Buzite, of the <x-word word="kindred"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #800000;">kindred</span></x-word> of <x-word word="ram"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #FF0000;">Ram</span></x-word>: against Job was his <x-word word="wrath"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #FF0000;">wrath</span></x-word> <x-word word="kindled"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #800000;">kindled</span></x-word>, because he justified himself rather than God.<br>那时，有布西人兰族巴拉迦的儿子以利户向约伯发怒，因约伯自以为义，不以 神为义。<br><br><br>伯32:3 <br>Also against his three friends was his <x-word word="wrath"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #FF0000;">wrath</span></x-word> <x-word word="kindled"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #800000;">kindled</span></x-word>, because they had found no answer, and yet had condemned Job.<br>他又向约伯的三个朋友发怒，因为他们想不出回答的话来，仍以约伯为有罪。<br><br><br>伯32:4 <br>Now <x-word word="elihu"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #0000FF;">Elihu</span></x-word> had <x-group group="waitXtill"><span style="box-shadow: 0px 3px white, 0px 4px #00BFFF;">waited till</span></x-group> Job had spoken, because they were <x-word word="elder"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #FF0000;">elder</span></x-word> than he.<br>以利户要与约伯说话，就等候他们，因为他们比自己年老。<br><br><br>伯32:5 <br>When <x-word word="elihu"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #0000FF;">Elihu</span></x-word> saw that there was no answer in the mouth of these three men, then his <x-word word="wrath"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #FF0000;">wrath</span></x-word> was <x-word word="kindled"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #800000;">kindled</span></x-word>.<br>以利户见这三个人口中无话回答，就怒气发作。<br><br><br>伯32:6 <br>And <x-word word="elihu"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #0000FF;">Elihu</span></x-word> the son of <x-word word="barachel"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #0000FF;">Barachel</span></x-word> the Buzite answered and said, I am young, and ye are very old; <x-word word="wherefore"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #800000;">wherefore</span></x-word> I was afraid, and <x-word word="durst"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #0000FF;">durst</span></x-word> not <x-word word="shew"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #800000;">shew</span></x-word> you mine opinion.<br>布西人巴拉迦的儿子以利户回答说：“我年轻，你们老迈，因此我退让，不敢向你们陈说我的意见。<br><br><br>伯32:7 <br>I said, Days should speak, and <x-word word="multitude"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #FF0000;">multitude</span></x-word> of years should teach wisdom.<br>我说：'年老的当先说话；寿高的当以智慧教训人。'<br><br><br>伯32:8 <br>But there is a spirit in man: and the <x-word word="inspiration"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #FF0000;">inspiration</span></x-word> of <x-group group="theXalmighty"><span style="box-shadow: 0px 3px white, 0px 4px #00BFFF;">the <x-word word="almighty"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #FF0000;">Almighty</span></x-word></span></x-group> <x-word word="giveth"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #0000FF;">giveth</span></x-word> them understanding.<br>但在人里面有灵；全能者的气使人有聪明。<br><br><br>伯32:9 <br>Great men are not always wise: neither do the aged understand judgment.<br>尊贵的不都有智慧；寿高的不都能明白公平。<br><br><br>伯32:10 <br>Therefore I said, <x-group group="hearkenXto"><span style="box-shadow: 0px 3px white, 0px 4px #00BFFF;"><x-word word="hearken"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #800000;">Hearken</span></x-word> to</span></x-group> me; I also will <x-word word="shew"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #800000;">shew</span></x-word> mine opinion.<br>因此我说：你们要听我言，我也要陈说我的意见。<br><br><br>伯32:11 <br><x-word word="behold"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #FF0000;">Behold</span></x-word>, I waited for your words; I gave ear to your reasons, whilst ye searched out what to say.<br>你们查究所要说的话；那时我等候你们的话，侧耳听你们的辩论，<br><br><br>伯32:12 <br><x-word word="yea"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #800000;">Yea</span></x-word>, I attended <x-word word="unto"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #FF0000;">unto</span></x-word> you, and, <x-word word="behold"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #FF0000;">behold</span></x-word>, there was none of you that convinced Job, or that answered his words:<br>留心听你们。谁知你们中间无一人折服约伯，驳倒他的话。<br><br><br>伯32:13 <br><x-word word="lest"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #FF0000;">Lest</span></x-word> ye should say, We have found out wisdom: God <x-word word="thrusteth"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #0000FF;">thrusteth</span></x-word> him down, not man.<br>你们切不可说：'我们寻得智慧； 神能胜他，人却不能。'<br><br><br>伯32:14 <br>Now he <x-word word="hath"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #FF0000;">hath</span></x-word> not directed his words against me: neither will I answer him with your speeches.<br>约伯没有向我争辩，我也不用你们的话回答他。<br><br><br>伯32:15 <br>They were <x-word word="amazed"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #FF0000;">amazed</span></x-word>, they answered no more: they left off speaking.<br>他们惊奇，不再回答，一言不发。<br><br><br>伯32:16 <br>When I had waited, (for they <x-word word="spake"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #800000;">spake</span></x-word> not, but stood still, and answered no more;)<br>我岂因他们不说话，站住不再回答，仍旧等候呢？<br><br><br>伯32:17 <br>I said, I will answer also my part, I also will <x-word word="shew"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #800000;">shew</span></x-word> mine opinion.<br>我也要回答我的一分话，陈说我的意见。<br><br><br>伯32:18 <br>For I am full of matter, the spirit within me <x-word word="constraineth"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #0000FF;">constraineth</span></x-word> me.<br>因为我的言语满怀，我里面的灵激动我。<br><br><br>伯32:19 <br><x-word word="behold"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #FF0000;">Behold</span></x-word>, my belly is as wine which <x-word word="hath"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #FF0000;">hath</span></x-word> no <x-word word="vent"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #FF0000;">vent</span></x-word>; it is ready to burst like new bottles.<br>我的胸怀如盛酒之囊没有出气之缝，又如新皮袋快要破裂。<br><br><br>伯32:20 <br>I will speak, that I may be <x-word word="refreshed"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #FF0000;">refreshed</span></x-word>: I will open my lips and answer.<br>我要说话，使我舒畅，我要开口回答。<br><br><br>伯32:21 <br>Let me not, I pray you, accept any man's person, neither let me give <x-word word="flattering"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #FF0000;">flattering</span></x-word> titles <x-word word="unto"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #FF0000;">unto</span></x-word> man.<br>我必不看人的情面，也不奉承人。<br><br><br>伯32:22 <br>For I know not to give <x-word word="flattering"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #FF0000;">flattering</span></x-word> titles; in so doing my maker would soon take me away.<br>我不晓得奉承，若奉承，造我的主必快快除灭我。</p>

